		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />VC in SDTV mode outputs 240p video, just like an NES, but the color encoding and possibly the aspect ratio are different. Has anyone taken an oscilloscope to the output of VC to see the aspect ratio, horizontal scan rate, and vertical scan rate of the screen mode that VC uses? Is it anything like the output of a Famicom Titler, which generates RGB signals using a PlayChoice PPU and pipes that through a closer-to-spec NTSC encoder?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


